# ASP and SAT solver written in Python
# by Kristoffer Kleine (01226240)
# kristoffer.kleine@student.tuwien.ac.at

Usage
-----

For solving SAT instances given in dimacs format (some available under test/resources/sat):

$ python src/main.py --sat --dpll --instance path/to/instance # dpll-style yields all solutions (if any)
$ python src/main.py --sat --cdnl --instance path/to/instance # cdnl-style yields first solution (if any)

For ASP solving with the provided three toy examples under tests/resources/asp:

$ python src/main.py --asp --dpll --instance path/to/instance # dpll-style yields all solutions (if any)
$ python src/main.py --asp --cdnl --instance path/to/instance # cdnl-style yields first solution (if any)